Definition: An acronym is an abbreviation formed from the initial letters of other words and pronounced as a word (e.g. ASCII, NASA). This task is about reading the given pre-tokenized setence and predicting which token is an acronym. It is possible that the pre-tokenized sentence may contain more than one token as an acronym, in which case you must output the first acronym that you identify. Please note that the output should be the acronym not the long form of the acronym.
